product_name: NYX Professional MakeupBrow Blade and Shade Nano Brow Mechanical Pencil
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackGet nano-bladed brows with the NYX Professional Makeup Brow Blade and Shade Nano Brow Mechanical Pencil. This dual-ended pencil precisely fills & shades for a natural, defined look.
details: DetailsFeaturesGet sharp, nano-bladed brows with the NYX innovative dual-edged pencilThis 2-in-1 tip precisely fills and naturally shades for a salon-worthy look at homeSimply blade, flip, and shade for up to 16 hours of smudge and transfer-resistant wearAvailable in multiple shades, Brow Blade and Shade creates hairlike strokes and a natural shaded fillCruelty free and vegan formulaItem 2634475How To UseStep 1: BLADE IT! Define your brow and create hairlike strokes with the top edge of the pencil.Step 2: SHADE IT! Flip to wide flat side to shade in sparse areas.Step 3: Blend and comb brow hair.IngredientsBlonde: Hydrogenated Coco-Glycerides, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide, Synthetic Wax, Zinc Stearate, Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil, CI 77492 / Iron Oxides, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, CI 77491 / Iron Oxides, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Tribehenin, Copernicia Cerifera Cera / Carnauba Wax / Cire De Carnauba, Caprylic/Capric Glycerides.

reviews.headline: Breaks too easily

reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love this brow pencil! It's nano tip makes it perfect to be super precise. I think the product is well made and will last a long time. My brows feel great after application. The color is perfect for me!

reviews.headline: Pathetic
reviews.comments: Nothing about this pencil is worth the money. Such a bad product. Slippery , doesnt lasts long and the color tone is awful. Might add some more money and get a higher end pencil on sale

reviews.headline: I will try other brands
reviews.comments: Color is so thin. This is my third time I have used this brand. I really liked it. But the color seems to get thinner and thinner and I'm ready to try another brand.

reviews.headline: Shade range sucks
reviews.comments: I have never been able to use any NYX brow products because the shade range for darker blondes is always horrible. I bought the ash blonde shade and its still too light and warm on my dark blonde brows, but the taupe shade and cool ash brown shades look like they are for true brunettes from the swatch pics. Its kind of crazy how many shades are offered in this pencil but none will work for me since they jump from platinum to dark brown.

reviews.headline: Would not recommend
reviews.comments: I am a loyal user of the nyx micro brow pencil, ive used it for years and havent switched. My only con on the products is the roundness makes it hard to make precise lines but it does the job. That being said I descided to give the blade and shade a try. At first I loved it, the precision was great but than it began to break. Due to the design of the packaging you have to roll it up quite a bit to have acsess to the product and its broke off soooo many times. I think I lost maybe have the product from it breaking off. When a normal nyx micro brown would last me about a month or more this one only lasts me a week or two becaue of all the breakage. Im very disappointed.
reviews.nickname: The breaking on the Blade and Shade

reviews.headline: Brows on the Fly
reviews.comments: I actually picked this up by accident when I meant to grab the NYX powder pencil, but this was waaayy better. Ultra precise, foolproof application, and great pigment. You can't  go wrong for the price. Very similar to the Ulta brand slim brown pencil, but the slanted application tip sets this product apart from others! Way to go NYX! Do yourself a favor and but this!

reviews.headline: Love It!!!!
reviews.comments: I love love love this product however I felt like there was not enough product in the pencil. I use it almost every day, and I felt like I had gone through it way sooner than I should have.

faceoff_positive.comments:
The NYX Professional Makeup Blade and Shade Eyebrow Brush is a versatile tool that makes achieving flawless brows incredibly simple. Its dual-ended design combines precision and practicality, featuring a fine-tipped pencil on one end and a spoolie brush on the other.

The pencil's ultra-fine tip is perfect for creating hair-like strokes, allowing you to define and shape your brows with precision. The texture is smooth and creamy, making application effortless without smudging or tugging on the skin. The pigmentation is buildable, so you can go for a natural or more dramatic look depending on your preference.

The spoolie brush is soft yet firm enough to blend the product seamlessly and groom brows into place. It's great for creating a natural finish by softening any harsh lines or distributing the pigment evenly.

One standout feature is its long-lasting formula, which stays put throughout the day without fading or transferring, even in humid conditions. Additionally, the range of shades ensures there's a match for most hair colors and skin tones.

Overall, this brush is a must-have for anyone looking for a high-quality, affordable brow tool that delivers professional results. Whether you're a beginner or a brow expert, the NYX Blade and Shade Eyebrow Brush is worth adding to your makeup kit.
faceoff_positive.headline: Awesome

faceoff_negative.comments: I usually like nyx eyebrow products but this one felt a little short. It's not bad by any means but as someone who has very sparse brows I need something that is going to give the illusion of more hair on my brows. The shape of the pencil itself it odd I can see why they chose to do it that way but I prefer a traditional pencil instead of this. I received the shade taupe and it wasn't bad I might just need to try a different color. So far it's not a bad product but I can definitely say that there are better brow products out there. I would say if you just need something to add color and fill in then this might work.. if you don't have enough brow hairs this might not be the best at giving the illusion of more brow hairs.
faceoff_negative.headline: Decent brown pen
